# AegisX Project Progress Rule

Before starting any task in this repository:

- Read the relevant section of `docs/20260628_project_progress_tracking.md`.
- Identify which project goal, subgoal, checklist item, or risk the task belongs to.
- Use the current progress document as the source of truth before changing code, experiments, docs, or architecture.

After finishing any task in this repository:

- Update `docs/20260628_project_progress_tracking.md` with a concise record of:
  - what was completed;
  - what was not completed because of errors, constraints, missing dependencies, measurement limits, or design limits;
  - whether continuing in this direction is still promising, and the next useful step.
- Remove or rewrite outdated, contradictory, or no-longer-accurate progress content.
- Keep the progress document compact. Prefer replacing stale details with the latest conclusion instead of appending long historical notes.
- If an experiment was run, record only the important result and the experiment output path.
- If a goal is blocked or no longer useful, mark it clearly rather than leaving it as an open TODO.

The progress document should stay short, current, and decision-oriented. It is not a raw log.
